NYT review of David Brock book skims over extensive criticism of NYT - Worldnews.com

 The New York Times today published a typically well-reasoned review of David Brock’s new book, “Killing the Messenger,” which savages the media for overly critical coverage of the Clintons and emphasizes the need for strong responses to attacks from conservative operatives and media outlets. Written by author Hanna Rosin, the review rightly chides Brock for […] ...

