Donald Trump spokeswoman Katrina Pierson and David Brock, a Hillary Clinton surrogate, battled on CNN tonight over what Brock called Trump’s bigoted, sexist, and “really dangerous” rhetoric.

Brock said last night that Trump’s “schlonged” attack on Clinton was about portraying President Obama as “a black rapist.” He didn’t repeat that tonight, but he did go after Trump as a “sad and pathetic” opportunist who’s playing the GOP like a fiddle.

Pierson shot back that Clinton and other liberals whine “like 9-year-old little girls” whenever someone like Trump dares be politically incorrect. Brock said, “Don’t tell me it’s politically correct, it’s just decent.”

Pierson defiantly said Trump is doing well because he isn’t a “soft person” who backs away from attacks from the liberal media....
Donald Trump spokeswoman Katrina Pierson and David Brock, a Hillary Clinton surrogate, battled on CNN tonight over what Brock called Trump’s bigoted, sexist, and “really dangerous” rhetoric.

