Panelists Michele Bachmann and David Brock discuss Donald Trump’s rise in the polls and Clinton’s reaction to Trump with host Don Lemon. Part 1. Side note, Brock has a new book coming out this week, Killing the Messenger. Bachmann argues the hot topics right now are the Iran deal and illegal immigration, which Donald Trump has come out strongly against. Brock argues what is dominating the Republican primaries is not the issues but Trump’s bullying of other candidates. Lemon asks Brock what he thinks of Clinton firing back at Trump over his sexist attacks against his GOP primary rival Carly Fiorina. In a clip, Clinton said she’s loved to debate Trump. Brock notes the polls are ephemeral and this race is a marathon but the GOP brand has been tremendously damaged by Trump. Bachmann tries to talk about immigration instead of answering questions on Trump’s sexist attacks on Fiorina and Brock calls her out it. Lemon poses the question to Bachmann again. Bachmann: “Well this is an old meme about a war on women…” Lemon rephrases the question on Trump’s war on women, especially with his latest comments on Carly Fiorina’s “face.” Bachmann: “I think like all this kind of stuff is nonsense…people want to have a good life and this is what it’s about.” Lemon moves on and asks Brock about a possible debate between Trump and Clinton. Brock: “Trump is a bully… I think there is no contest…” Bachmann pivots to talking about the Iran deal instead of Trump. Then they discuss the Iran deal and the controversy over Clinton’s use of a private email server during her tenure as Secretary of State. L...
